fields.value: 1. NY, Manhattan: Lower East Side 19th c
Immigrant Ghetto: New York’s Lower East Side

The realm of the Bowery and Lower East Side was that of the “undesirables” – foreign, uneducated, degenerate. So, the Ghetto was low on all levels: geographically, socially, and morally. Immigrant families, overcrowded in their tenement housing, could little afford leisurely commodities. Even young children would have to help on “home work” – low skill labor done at home as part of the booming textile and garment industries.  It was a relentless struggle to assimilate and move up and out of the Ghetto.
